# Antigravity Rules

## Critical Instructions
- **ALWAYS** read the [Project Design Guide](docs/design_guide.md) before writing any code or making design decisions.
- Ensure all UI components align with the brand guidelines defined in the design guide.
- Use the `User` model instead of `Admin` for all user-related operations, but keep the "Admin Portal" terminology for the back-office UI.

## Color Usage
- **NO DIRECT HEX CODES**: Do not use hex color codes (e.g., `#fafaf8`, `#2a2a2a`) directly in `className` attributes.
- **USE SEMANTIC CLASSES**: Always use the semantic Tailwind classes defined in `app/globals.css` and `tailwind.config.ts`.
  - Backgrounds: `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `bg-popover`, `bg-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `bg-muted`, `bg-accent`, `bg-destructive`
  - Text: `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-primary-foreground`, `text-secondary-foreground`, `text-destructive-foreground`, `text-accent-foreground`
  - Borders: `border-border`, `border-input`, `border-ring`
  - Primary Color (Gold): `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-primary`

## User Feedback
- **ALWAYS USE TOASTS**: Implement toast notifications for all success and error messages using `useToast` hook.
- **ERROR HANDLING**: For errors and failed requests, always use the `destructive` variant (red) and include a "Try again" action button where applicable.
  - Very Light Gray (#f5f5f3) → `bg-secondary`, `bg-muted`, or `bg-accent`
  - Error Red (#d32f2f) → `bg-destructive`, `text-destructive`, `border-destructive`
- Before writing color classes, verify the correct semantic class by checking `app/globals.css` CSS variables and `tailwind.config.ts` color definitions.
